{"key":"processedPost-20002235","value":{"id":20002235,"first":19979607,"last":20946217,"when":1400361430,"utime":"05/18/14 12:17 AM","cleanedPost":"Casing mixes should be non-nutritious or they're considered additional layers of substrate, not casing.<br />You don't want a casing layer to fully colonize.&nbsp; The uncolonized parts hold water until the colonized parts can absorb it into the mycelium.&nbsp; If you use substrate material as a casing, it fully colonizes.<br />One drawback which may have happened above is the time between spawning the bulk substrate and applying the casing layer allows a lot of time for contaminant spores to land on the surface.&nbsp; They're then protected while they germinate and begin to grow under the casing.<br />RR"}}